== Ternary Conditional ifn ==

The ternary conditional ifn is an operation that chooses between two numbers depending on whether
or not a boolean expression is true. The operation is defined [/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/df-ifn | here].

When φ is true, [/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/ifn1 | ifn φ A B = A].
When φ is false, [/edit/peano/peano_thms.gh/ifn2 | ifn φ A B = B	].


